how's that?
rubixhacker , I assume material backport libs?

I was using third-party ones that were filling the gap.  MaterialEditText is now replaced by TextInputLayout. I was using a Floating Action Button library, and a Tab strip library. A few weeks ago appcompat added Dialogs which replaced the MaterialDialogs library.
So it's a good news, first it sounded like it was a bad one
Yeah totally, I am glad that other devs provided these awesome libraries, and that Google finally got simple things like a FAB in appcompat.
yeah, google should have worked that out last year when they announced L and material, not a whole year later
I think google didn’t expect the need for FAB as it’s basically just an imagebutton/imageview

I agree, appcompat should've been released last year with the full suite of views. As far as the FAB goes I understand their view but it also has some complicated things like shadow and elevation that are hard to get right on older platforms.  Also by not providing  a view for it each developer implementing it has to recreate the wheel each time. The FAB's look and behavior is going to vary between apps.
